9. Replit Secrets

Never store API keys inside source code.

Instead, Replit provides Secrets.

Example

Key

GEMINI_API_KEY

Value

AIzaSyxxxxxxxxxxxx

Python reads it securely.

10. Why Use Secrets?

Wrong

api_key = "AIzaSy123456"

Problems:

Visible in GitHub
Security risk
Easy to misuse

Correct

Replit Secrets

↓

Python

↓

Gemini API
11. Python Reads Secrets

Python reads the secret using environment variables.

Example

import os

api_key = os.getenv("GEMINI_API_KEY")

This keeps sensitive information out of your code.

